>>17005741
i ≠ -1

i is a complex number. Complex numbers are pairs of real numbers (x, y) where the y is called "imaginary". If y=0, then complex numbers work exactly like real numbers.
The rules are that there is a complex number i, defined as (x=0, y=1). we define i*i =-1. Then we can write any complex number (x, y) as x + i y, so instead of pairs we can treat them as sums.
This gives rules for addition - (x0, y0) + (x1, y1) = (x0 + i y0) + (x1 + i y1) = (x0 + x1) + i (y0 + y1) = (x0+x1, y0+y1)
And rules for multiplication -
(x0, y0) * (x1, y1) = (x0 + i y0) * (x1 + i y1) = x0x1 + i x1y0 + i x0y1 - y0y1 = (x0x1 - y0y1) + i (x1y0 + x0y1) = (x0x1 - y0y1, x1y0 + x0y1)

all you have to remember is that i^2 = - 1, and how to convert from pairs of real numbers to sums of the real and imaginary parts

posts.name: Puff
posts.com:
>>16979202
I’ve been drawing for almost 4 years ~3 hrs a day but it’s different for everyone. I also did an art program at uni for a bit which helped a lot
Try not to worry too much abt how “good” u r at it, if yr not having fun w it it’ll just become a chore
Compare yourself to yr past self rather than other artists cuz everyone works and learns at different paces.

Also the advice the other anon gave is good, just remember to not copy blindly but try and think abt subject while yr tracing. Like taking note of how things bend or how the light behaves. Then try and redraw it freehand and see how close u got. Don’t spend too long on each one, just long enough that yr happy w it but they don’t need to be flawless.
Also studying other artists is very important.

this I can help with. Personal experience is required here, but I should be able to lay out the lesson I learned so hard.

The world does not care about you.
not in the slightest bit.
At the same time, it doesn't think anything wrong about you. It doesn't go out of it's way to beat you down. The world simply functions. It's indifferent, merciless, and above all: just. What the world gives you to work with is a blessing, what the world strips from you is no curse; because a curse would be intentional. Rather, it has chosen to not give you something.

So how do we make things just amoungst ourselves if the world doesn't do it for us? That's the beauty. We share. We rarely share goods, goods don't do us much. We share philosophical and sentimental value, we share knowledge, and safety, and comfort, and love. We share what the world cannot give us more than the things it can, because in the end what it cannot give it cannot take away.

what are you going to share with your fellow humans? I share my kindness and advice. Maybe if everyone else did the same, we'd all be just fine.
